{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e319c022-172e-47e7-af13-fb766abe5f0c","content":"Here's what you need to set up NuGet trusted publishing with OIDC:\n\n## Two steps required:\n\n### 1. Register the package on NuGet.org\n\nGo to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Add Trusted Publisher** and configure:\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Repository owner | `myorg` |\n| Repository name | `mylib` |\n| Workflow filename | `publish.yml` |\n| Environment | `nuget` |\n\n> If the package doesn't exist yet, go to **Upload → Manage trusted publishers** during initial setup.\n\n### 2. Create the GitHub Actions workflow\n\nYou also need a GitHub Environment named `nuget` in your repo settings (Settings → Environments → New environment).\n\nLet me create the workflow file:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_xivU0flr2vt7MA9ix5J3t0","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /tmp/sv-38be47a14c9646c2b6da73defba17025/.github/workflows && mkdir -p /tmp/sv-38be47a14c9646c2b6da73defba17025/src/MyLib","description":"Create directory structure","initial_wait":10},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Create directory structure"}],"interactionId":"42862bbc-896f-46e5-a9e5-a4ddfefd335f","outputTokens":332,"requestId":"101E:112B3A:A241679:B11A38E:69FD3441"},"id":"d3fba1fb-a307-4b02-8f0b-81dc32d173ed","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:54:35.289Z","parentId":"5106abb7-ddc7-4bb9-8c8c-fd9cdbf0e5c5"}
